A trypsin that is a serine protease of the granules from mast cells, cytotoxic T lymphocytes and/or natural killer cells. Leukocyte granule-associated proteinase is a component of the immune system that protect higher organisms against viral infection and cellular transformation. Members of this class have features that are strongly conserved including: consensus sequences at their N-termini and around the three catalytic residues, activation from zymogenic forms, and conserved disulphide bridges.
A protein that contains one copy of the T-box domain (Pfam:PF00907) and it is involved in the anterior neural specification.
A protein that is a translation product of a fusion of two genes.

A chimeric protein that consists of part of the human CREBBP gene at the N terminus and part of the human KAT6B gene at the C-terminus. This form is observed in some cases of acute myelogenous leukemia where chromosomal translocation occurs.

A chimeric protein that consists of part of the human KAT6B gene at the N terminus and part of the human CREBBP gene at the C-terminus. It includes the zinc fingers, 2 nuclear localization signals, the histone acetyltransferase (HAT) domain, a portion of the acidic domain of KAT6B and the zinc fingers, KIX domain, bromodomain and CREB-binding domain from CREBBP. This form is observed in some cases of acute myelogenous leukemia where chromosomal translocation occurs.
